        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt chocolate and mix",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C (160°C fan). Line a 20 cm square tin with baking paper. Melt {{dark-chocolate}} and {{unsalted-butter}} together and leave to cool for 5 minutes. Whisk {{eggs}}, {{caster-sugar}}, and {{vanilla-extract}} together in a large bowl until combined, 1 minute, no need to beat to ribbons for the cakey style. Stir in the melted chocolate mixture. Fold in {{plain-flour}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{salt-table}} until just combined.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake and cool",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour into the tin and bake for 25 to 28 minutes until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean with no raw batter clinging to it. The top should be set and the sides pulling away slightly from the tin. Leave in the tin to cool for at least 30 minutes before cutting. For neat squares, refrigerate for 1 hour then cut with a sharp knife.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
